summary:
The Security Council,
Welcoming the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations operation in Cyprus, 
Reaffirms all its relevant resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999) and subsequent resolutions;
Decides to extend the mandate of UNFICYP until 15 June 2004;
Urges the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to lift all remaining restrictions on UNFICYP;
Expresses concern over continuing violations at Strovilia, urging restoration of the pre-30 June 2000 military status quo;
Requests a report by 1 June 2004 on implementation;
Decides to remain seized of the matter.
